    <div class="AssessmentProblem.identifier">102782</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.type">ShortAnswerResponse</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.statement"><p>Here is a tape diagram representing the amount of tomato pur&#xE9;e and the amount of chopped basil in a pizza sauce recipe.</p>

<p><img class="h-max-height--4-lines" src="/image_files/29503.png" /></p>

<ol>
	<li>How many cups of tomato pur&#xE9;e are in this batch?</li>
	<li>How many cups of ingredients are in the entire batch?</li>
	<li>Andre is using 16 cups of tomato pur&#xE9;e. How many cups of basil will he use if he follows the recipe? Show or explain your reasoning.</li>
</ol>
</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.solution"><ol>
	<li>12 cups</li>
	<li>15 cups</li>
	<li>4 cups, because <span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="47637">\(16\div4=4\)</span>, so each unit is worth 4 cups.</li>
</ol>
</div>
